# 🧠 Learning Philosophy

This project is learning-first.

Every major feature should explain:

* Why it exists
* How it works
* Internal request flow
* Architecture
* Trade-offs
* Production considerations
* Alternatives
* Common implementation mistakes

Understanding the engineering principles is considered as important as implementing the feature itself.

---

# 🏗️ Architecture Principles

Every implementation should follow these principles (see `architecture.mdc` for how each is enforced):

* Modular Architecture
* Provider Abstraction
* Configuration-Driven Design
* Separation of Concerns
* Dependency Injection
* Project-Scoped Isolation
* Version Everything
* Background Processing
* Observability First
* Security by Design
* Scalability
* Testability
* Reusability

Business applications should never depend directly on AI vendors or AI infrastructure.

